cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with object shape representation and shape retrieval, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of statistical relationships and clustering algorithms also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The graph theoretic approach and use of minimum description length principle indicate a potential fit for graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the use of image datasets suggests a possible fit for multimedia (cs.MM).
